The Herald LONDON. — Novak Djokovic has equalled Steffi Graf’s record for most weeks as world number one after starting his 377th week at the top of the men’s tennis rankings. The 35-year-old Serb has held the record for the most weeks as men’s world number one since March 2021. Yesterday, he moved level with Germany’s Graf, who first rose to the top of the women’s rankings in 1987.  Rankings 